A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 40-2-151 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 annual license fees for operation of vehicles, fee for permanent licensing of certain trailers,
3 and fee for new passenger car with paid title ad valorem taxes, so as to provide for the
4 issuance of separate license plates for hearses and ambulances; to provide for related matters;
5 to provide for an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 40-2-151 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to annual license
9 fees for operation of vehicles, fee for permanent licensing of certain trailers, and fee for new
10 passenger car with paid title ad valorem taxes, is amended in subsection (a) by revising
11 paragraph (12) and adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
12 "(12) For each motor driven hearse or ambulance . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 20.00
13 (12.1) For each motor driven ambulance . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 20.00"
14 SECTION 2.
15 This Act shall become effective on January 1, 2026.
